1
00:59:47,002 --> 00:59:50,337
[IN ENGLISH]
Welcome, Thorin, son of Thrain.

2
00:59:50,505 --> 00:59:52,923
I do not believe we have met.

3
00:59:53,425 --> 00:59:56,469
You have your grandfather's bearing.

4
00:59:56,636 --> 00:59:59,138
I knew Thror
when he ruled Under the Mountain.

5
00:59:59,306 --> 01:00:02,600
Indeed? He made no mention of you.

6
01:00:06,063 --> 01:00:12,063
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

7
01:00:13,779 --> 01:00:16,072
GLOIN:
What is he saying?

8
01:00:16,239 --> 01:00:18,699
Does he offer us insult?

9
01:00:18,867 --> 01:00:22,536
No, Master Gloin, he's offering you food.

10
01:00:24,372 --> 01:00:26,373
[ALL MURMURING]

11
01:00:29,211 --> 01:00:32,797
Well, in that case, lead on.

12
01:00:33,799 --> 01:00:34,840
BOFUR:
Hey. Come on.

13
01:00:35,050 --> 01:00:37,968
Try it. Just a mouthful.

14
01:00:38,136 --> 01:00:39,720
I don't like green food.

15
01:00:40,889 --> 01:00:41,931
Where's the meat?

16
01:00:42,099 --> 01:00:43,349
[GROWLS]

17
01:00:43,558 --> 01:00:45,059
Have they got any chips?

18
01:00:46,269 --> 01:00:48,521
Kind of you to invite us.

19
01:00:48,688 --> 01:00:50,272
Not really dressed for dinner.

20
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:51,690
Well, you never are.

21
01:00:51,858 --> 01:00:53,400
[GANDALF CHUCKLES]

22
01:01:01,201 --> 01:01:02,535
[DWARVES CHUCKLING]

23
01:01:10,377 --> 01:01:11,836
[CHUCKLES]

24
01:01:12,420 --> 01:01:16,507
This is Orcrist, the Goblin-cleaver.

25
01:01:16,675 --> 01:01:18,300
A famous blade...

26
01:01:18,468 --> 01:01:24,348
...forged by the High Elves of the West,
my kin.

27
01:01:24,516 --> 01:01:26,433
May it serve you well.

28
01:01:26,601 --> 01:01:29,019
And this is Glamdring...

29
01:01:30,689 --> 01:01:34,525
...the Foehammer.
Sword of the King of Gondolin.

30
01:01:34,693 --> 01:01:37,111
These swords were made for
the Goblin Wars of the First Age.

31
01:01:37,279 --> 01:01:42,199
I wouldn't bother, laddie. Swords are
named for the great deeds they do in war.

32
01:01:42,367 --> 01:01:44,618
What are you saying,
my sword hasn't seen battle?

33
01:01:45,162 --> 01:01:47,163
I'm not actually sure it is a sword.

34
01:01:48,582 --> 01:01:50,499
More of a letter opener, really.

35
01:01:51,585 --> 01:01:53,002
How did you come by these?

36
01:01:53,170 --> 01:01:56,130
We found them in a Troll-hoard
on the Great East Road...

